# pytest E2E Conventions

## Markers

Every test must have at least one `@pytest.mark.<fr_id>` marker linking it to an SRS requirement (FR-1 through FR-35). Non-functional tests use `nfr_perf` or `nfr_compat`.

```python
@pytest.mark.fr8
class TestDailyChallengeDisplay:
    def test_shows_three_pokemon(self, clean_page):
        """FR-8: Daily challenge screen displays exactly 3 Pokemon cards."""
```

## Test Structure

- Class-based grouping: one test class per logical feature area
- Docstrings on every test method referencing the SRS requirement ID
- Use fixtures from `conftest.py` (`clean_page`, `seeded_page`, etc.)

## Fixtures

- `clean_page` -- fresh browser page with cleared cookies
- `seeded_page` -- page with a voter_token cookie that has already voted today
- `base_url` -- the app URL (session-scoped)
- `api_url` -- the API URL (session-scoped)

## File Naming

- `test_daily_challenge.py` -- FR-8 to FR-11 (display)
- `test_voting.py` -- FR-12 to FR-18 (voting flow)
- `test_identity.py` -- FR-19 to FR-22 (anonymous identity)
- `test_results.py` -- FR-23 to FR-28 (results display)
- `test_daily_reset.py` -- FR-29 to FR-32 (daily reset)
- `test_history.py` -- FR-33 to FR-35 (history)
